Here is a great exercise you can do to upgrade your chipping motion!😊

Trail hand only, lead hand only, and put those feels together with both hands on. The engine of this motion is your chest, try to have an even sided motion back and through!

This is a great drill to work on completing your backswing by turning the chest vs lifting with the arms. It is also a great visual for maintaining side bend by having a visual check point on the finish. ⛳️😊

Do practice swings FIRST to get acquainted with the drill!  When you hit shots: Smooth swings with limited power, this is an exercise that requires discipline and the correct intention. The intention is to hit the ball half the distance you normally would. I recommend using a 7 or 8 iron max! 😁

Here is a great drill to keep your swing plane in check. ✅😊

This drill prevents your hands from working too far away from you on the initial downswing. If you are too steep “ over the top”, you will hit the stick on the downswing. It will also help if you get stuck and early extend. ( handle raising through impact)

Here is a fun drill to help use the ground effectively. 💣⛳️

1. Place alignment stick in the ground on a slight angle. Stand one fist length away. The end of the stick should be in line with your trail thigh. 

2. Launch the stick out of the ground by pressing into the turf with your front foot to initiate. Maintain your posture on the finish. 

3. Replicate the stick launch feeling with a club 😊👊

Building blocks! Here is a great exercise to isolate a few movements and blend them together fluidly. Start out rehearsing the follow through without a club, then rehearse the same feeling with the club. Next, add a little energy on the backswing and rehearse the same feeling on the finish without a club. Then execute that motion over the ball. 

These are small swings to help create the correct impact and balanced finish. Start adding more backswing and energy once you’ve hit them solidly with a controlled swing and pace. 👊⛳️

Here is a good one to help upgrade your overall swing! The explanation of how it reinforces/creates positive movements are in the video! 👊⛳️

Set up:
1. Cut a pool noodle in half
2. Poke a hole in the center of the pool noodle with an alignment stick. Secure the noodle to the alignment rod using a hair tie or rubber band. ( lol 😂)
4. Place the alignment stick (with noodle attached ) in the ground at the angle of the club shaft you’re using. Provide enough space for your hands. ( the noodle should rest about 1 foot above your club shaft at address.

Hi Everyone! I’m excited to announce that I’m teaming up with Taylormade to help increase awareness for the non-profit organization Youth On Course! ( Keep reading for Taylormade Giveaway 🤩⛳️)

This cause is close to my heart and I’m grateful to be a part of it. Golf has shaped the core aspects of my character, and has taught me many lessons outside of the game. I hope to give back and provide others with that same chance.

This amazing non-profit is about ACCESS and AFFORDABILITY for kids across the country by subsidizing rounds so it costs just $5 or less for kids to play. This provides juniors from diverse backgrounds with the exposure and opportunity they may not have had otherwise.

I’m using my resources to spread awareness for this cause. Please hit the donate button if you can, or even sharing this post will make an impact. Every little bit counts and together we can make a huge difference in their lives! To view my fundraising page, please click the link in my bio! 🙏

Impact visual ⛳️😊

Give this drill a try if you need help creating forward shaft lean at impact. Do this drill with a smaller swing at a relaxed pace… 😅  Feel that your handle leads the club head the entire time through the hitting zone. 

How to set up the drill:

Visually from face on-
Alignment stick in the ground slightly in front of the ball, about in line with where your lead foot would be. 
Down the line-
Stick in the ground on a slight angle ( about the angle of the club you’re using), with enough room to freely swing.
